        "order": 27
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_yanbaor2_yanbaoPPT_469_26",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Source: McKinsey analysis",
        "bbox": [
          0.2603550286837246,
          0.5900297619592677,
          0.3786982227955654,
          0.597470238149744
        ],
        "order": 28
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_yanbaor2_yanbaoPPT_469_27",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Many grocers have made great progress on analytical maturity. Leaders in analytics have tackled the majority of fundamental use cases, such as pricing, mass promotion, and assortment optimization. Now they have increasingly turned their focus to pursuing new use cases along the value chain and improving existing use cases-for example, by using more granular, realtime data. These efforts are often driven by a strong analytics unit, but the level of adoption across a business varies.",
        "bbox": [
          0.25838263807402545,
          0.6497093021221141,
          0.5779092639229592,
          0.8924418604909525
        ],
        "order": 29
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_yanbaor2_yanbaoPPT_469_28",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The best analytics solution does not help if it is not used and understood by the respective decision makers, such as category managers.",
        "bbox": [
          0.5976331371119316,
          0.6497093022214357,
          0.9132149812312641,
          0.725287868690357
        ],
        "order": 30
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_yanbaor2_yanbaoPPT_469_29",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "In many cases, organizational maturity is the main barrier to going beyond partial adoption and realizing the full potential of analytics. It encompasses both the process of technically embedding and continually improving use cases, as well as the process of enacting constant change management regarding the",
        "bbox": [
          0.5956607518465779,
          0.7455357144819038,
          0.9171597613191027,
          0.8953488375169365
        ],
        "order": 31
      }
    ]
